[h1]val()[/h1]

We have seen in the previous lesson how we can manipulate the content of HTML elements using the [b]text()[/b] and [b]html()[/b] methods.
Another useful method is the [b]val()[/b] method, which allows us to get and set the values of form fields, such as textboxes, dropdowns, and similar inputs. 
[b]For Example:
HTML: [/b] [code format="html" ]<input type="text" id="name" value="Your Name">[/code]
[b]JS:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="1110"]$(function() {
  alert($("#name").[b]val()[/b]);
});
//alerts "Your Name"[/code]
Similarly, you can set the value for the field by providing it as a parameter to the [b]val()[/b] method.
[note]Getting and setting form field values is very useful when you need to handle form events and validation. We will cover events later in the course.[/note]
